data.title: SOUTHERN SECTION
data.meta_description: Saturday, Oct. 23 AYALA TOURNAMENT Gold Division Championship Western Christian d.
data.text:
OMEGE LEAGUE

First Lutheran d. Camarillo Cornerston Christian, 25-19, 25-18, 25-22

Danielle Alba had five aces and 21 digs and Christina Aguilera had 15 assists for Cornerstone Christian (4-7, 4-6). First Lutheran improved to 11-0 and 9-0 in league.

PREP LEAGUE

Westridge d. Rio Hondo Prep, 25-16, 25-15, 25-22

Senior Zandie Brockett and sophomore Kelly McCall tied for the kill lead with six each for visiting Westridge (14-5, 5-4). Sophomore Annie Thorne had 23 assists and sophomore Kyle Floyd had four blocks for the Tigers.

Nicole Day had 11 kills and 20 digs for Rio Hondo Prep (7-9, 0-9). Laura Lammers had 14 digs and Jessica Horton had 23 assists for the Kares.

VICTORY LEAGUE

Baptist Christian d. Moreno Valley Calvary Chapel, 25-8, 25-10, 25-12

Kellie Dekiewiet had 15 kills to lead visiting Baptist Christian (4-1 league).

Mesa Grande Academy d. Bloomington Christian, 22-25, 25-23, 25-17, 25-11

Felicia Brown had eight kills and three aces for Bloomington Christian (4-8, 2-4), but the Ravens fell in a match at Mesa Grande Academy (2-4 in league play).

Thursday, Oct. 21

AGAPE LEAGUE

Bethel Christian d. Joshua Springs, 25-17, 26-24, 25-23

Julie Stilson had 11 kills and eight digs, Sarah Scheuer added six kills and Crystal Kady finished with 22 assists and six digs for host Bethel Christian (12-5, 5-1). Joshua Springs is 4-11 and 2-4.

Hesperia Christian d. Antelope Valley Christian, 25-6, 25-13, 25-9

Laura Gustin had seven kills and two blocks, Alex Chatfield had seven kills and four aces and Casey Shattuck had 19 assists for visiting Hesperia Christian (8-2, 6-0), ranked No. 2 in Division V-AA.

ALPHA LEAGUE

Grace Brethren d. L.A. Baptist, 29-27, 25-21, 19-25, 25-23

Caitlin Barshaw had eight kills and three aces and Kristina Bennett added 29 assists to lead visiting Grace Brethren (18-5, 3-2). L.A. Baptist fell to 2-3 in league play

BASELINE LEAGUE

Upland d. Los Osos, 25-17, 26-24, 25-23

Megan Wong had nine kills for visiting Los Osos (8-8, 3-3) against Upland (6-0 in league).

BAY LEAGUE

Redondo d. Leuzinger, 25-13, 25-10, 25-15

Teuila Barnes of Leuzinger (0-6, 0-6) had three kills and two blocks at Redondo.

CAMINO REAL LEAGUE

St. Matthias d. Gardena Serra, 25-9, 25-9, 25-20

Senior outside hitter Marleni Garcia had three kills, 10 aces and 13 service points for host St. Matthias (9-2, 5-0). Serra falls to 0-5 in league.

CENTURY LEAGUE

Anaheim Canyon d. Tustin, 25-22, 20-25, 25-18, 21-25, 15-7

Senior outside hitter Lindsay Lakso had 31 kills, Mallorie Martinez had 58 assists and senior outside hitter Lauren Brooks had 50 digs to lead Anaheim Canyon (4-7, 2-4) at Tustin (2-9, 0-6).

Brea Olinda d. Villa Park, 20-25, 25-17, 23-25, 25-21, 15-2

Rachel Lumsden had 31 kills and three aces, Nikki Awaa had 53 assists, 11 digs and four blocks and Amy Fink had 27 digs to lead Brea Olinda (5-13, 4-2) at Villa Park (3-3).

El Dorado d. El Modena, 25-15, 25-18, 25-20

Shannan Homan had 16 kills and Jamie Friedrich added 12 kills while sister Jenna Friedrich had 34 assists for El Dorado (9-3, 6-0) in its victory at El Modena (3-3 in league).

CHRISTIAN LEAGUE

Ontario Christian d. Aquinas, 25-20, 25-16, 25-22

Stacy Nanninga had 16 kills, Alexa Antoni added 22 assists and Alyssa DeGroot had 14 digs for host Ontario Christian (5-7, 3-4)

DE ANZA LEAGUE

Beaumont d. Yucca Valley, 25-22, 25-19, 25-13

Jessica Granados and Sarah Henry had 10 kills apiece to lead Beaumont (11-3. 8-3). Host Yucca Valley (4-9, 3-8) was led by Katie Naylor with four kills and one ace.

Big Bear d. Beaumont Banning, 25-13, 25-12, 21-25, 23-25, 15-1

Madison Bradley had 18 kills, nine digs and three aces and Kinsey Fulton had nine aces, eight kills and nine digs to lead host Big Bear (6-8, 5-6). Banning dropped to 0-14, 0-11.

DELPHIC LEAGUE

Crossroads d. Montclair Prep, 25-18, 25-12, 25-15

Sophomore Jessi Brown had 12 assists and eight aces for host Crossroads (8-3, 5-0). Montclair Prep is 2-3 in league.

Pacific Hills d. Pasadena Marshall, 25-19, 25-12, 25-21

Michelle Krief, Abbey Lane and Helen Suarez each had six aces and Suarez finished with 10 digs to lead host Pacific Hills (7-6, 4-2) over Marshall.

DEL REY LEAGUE

St. Monica d. Cantwell, 25-9, 25-12, 25-10

Host St. Monica improved its record to 9-8, 2-3.

DEL RIO LEAGUE

California d. Santa Fe, 25-17, 26-24, 25-22

Brianna Gonzales had 12 kills to lead California (13-2, 4-2) past host and league-leading Santa Fe (5-1 in league play).

EMPIRE LEAGUE

Loara d. La Palma Kennedy, 25-20, 25-23, 25-21

Clare Morgenstern had 10 kills and Carrie Flaming added nine of her own for host Loara (9-8, 4-2). Karla Andree had nine kills for Kennedy (9-11, 0-6)

Orange Lutheran d. Katella, 25-17, 25-22, 26-24

Adriana Bracamonte had seven kills in leading Orange Lutheran to the victory at Katella. Suzzie Rench had nine kills to lead Katella, which fell to 1-5 in league play. Orange Lutheran is 5-1 in league.

Placentia Valencia d. Cypress, 25-22, 25-22, 25-21

Jacque Davisson had 12 kills for host Valencia (9-13, 5-1). Cypress fell to 3-3 in league play.

FOOTHILL LEAGUE

Hart d. Burbank Burroughs, 16-25, 25-21, 25-20, 25-16

Amie Russ had 12 kills and 17 digs, Amanda Newton had 11 kills and Callie McIntosh had 15 digs as Hart (6-10, 3-3) rallied to win at home. Setter Jamie Long had 30 assists in running the Indian offense. Burroughs fell to 7-6 overall and 1-5 in league.

FRONTIER LEAGUE

Oaks Christian d. Nordhoff, 26-24, 25-14, 25-10

Julie Rubinstein had 23 kills and Ingrid Reimer had 34 assists as Oaks Christian (17-5, 4-1) avenged an earlier loss to Nordhoff and pulled into a first-place tie with the Rangers in its victory at home. Nordhoff won the first match between the teams in five games.

GARDEN GROVE

Rancho Alamitos d. Bolsa Grande, 22-25, 25-16, 25-18, 25-13

Host Rancho Alamitos improved its record to 12-2, 7-2.

GOLDEN LEAGUE

Quartz Hill d. Highland, 22-25, 25-15, 27-25, 25-19

Allison Tosch had 11 kills and 9 blocks. Summer Plante had 18 kills and Tara Henn had 9 kills to lead host Quartz Hill (8-4, 6-0). Highland fell to 3-3 in league play.

HARBOR LEAGUE

Lighthouse Christian d. Shalhevet, 25-10, 25-10, 25-8

Lighthouse Christian, which is ranked No. 6 in Division V-A, improves to 14-2 overall and 9-0 in league.

Ribet Academy d. Rolling Hills Prep, 28-30, 23-25, 25-22, 25-21, 16-14

Brijean Murphy had 14 kills and six aces, Shannon Wainwright had 12 kills and five aces and Janice Santa Ana finished with 26 assists for Ribet Academy (9-2, 7-2).

Sarah Keys had 12 kills and Jasmine Watts had five kills and five aces to lead host Rolling Hills Prep (5-6, 5-6).

INTERNATIONAL LEAGUE

Southwestern Academy d. Calvary Baptist, 25-20, 25-20, 27-29, 25-12

Alli Cole had 28 kills and eight aces and Sydni Davis had 19 kills and five aces to lead visisiting Southwestern Academy (8-2, 3-0) past Calvary Baptist (3-12, 3-1).

LIBERTY LEAGUE

Providence d. Buckley, 25-8, 25-9, 25-17

Heather Hansen had 10 kills and 18 digs and Vanessa Amran had 21 assists for visiting Providence (11-3, 7-1). Buckley drops to 7-4, 4-4.

Viewpoint d. Holy Martyrs, 25-5, 25-8, 25-17

Marisa Fair had 11 kills and five service aces and Jacie Dry had 22 assists and five kills to lead Viewpoint (9-2, 6-1) at Holy Martyrs (1-10, 0-6).

Windward d. Oakwood, 25-17, 25-23, 26-14

Junior Hailey Dumham of Windward (13-5, 7-1) had 15 kills and 13 assists at Oakwood.

MARMONTE LEAGUE

Moorpark d. Simi Valley, 25-11, 25-9, 15-25, 25-18

Kelley Hanson had 19 kills, 24 digs and 10 aces and Lauren Hartnett added 39 assists to lead host Moorpark (12-2, 9-1).

Royal d. Calabasas, 27-25, 25-23, 25-19

Christina Bussing had 10 kills and Jamie Nixon added 24 assists and 10 digs for visiting Royal, which improved to 4-5 in league. Val Kepler added five blocks and five kills for the Highlanders.

MISSION LEAGUE

Flintridge Sacred Heart d. Alemany, 25-15, 25-10, 25-15

Kelly Smiland had 11 kills and 11 digs to lead Flintridge Sacred Heart (13-2, 6-0), which is ranked No. 3 in Division IV-AA.

Sherman Oaks Notre Dame d. Chaminade, 18-25, 25-17, 25-22, 25-17

Senior Meredith Rice had 16 kills and 22 digs for visiting Sherman Oaks Notre Dame (9-2, 5-1), ranked No. 3 in the Southern Section Division III-A coaches’ poll. Chaminade is 1-5 in league.

MOJAVE RIVER LEAGUE

Rim of the World d. Hesperia, 25-21, 25-11, 25-4

Sonja Newcombe had 11 kills and four blocks and Nique Fradella finished with 30 assists for Rim of the World (17-0, 5-0), ranked No. 4 in Division III-AA.

OLYMPIC LEAGUE

Cerritos Valley Christian d. Whittier Christian, 25-17, 25-13, 25-20

Melissa Boer had nine kills, two blocks and four aces and Kelsee Larsen had four aces to lead host Valley Christian (13-5, 4-1).

Amber Garcia had seven kills and eight digs and Chistian Swaney had five kills and seven digs for Whittier Christian (4-13, 0-5).

Maranatha d. Village Christian, 25-19, 25-17, 25-10

Lolo Vanderlaan and Lauren Fields each had six kills to lead host Maranatha (9-7, 3-2). Village Christian dropped to 1-4 in league.

ORANGE LEAGUE

Savanna d. Magnolia, 25-13, 25-22, 25-15

Maggie Shoukry had 14 kills and Jessica Gaxiola had 12 kills to lead Savanna (11-1, 6-0) at Magnolia (2-9, 2-4).

PACIFIC LEAGUE

Arcadia d. Pasadena, 25-15, 25-22, 25-12

Ashley Nick of Arcadia (9-2, 6-0) had nine kills and teammate Lisa Buchicchio added six aces against visiting Pasadena (9-4, 4-2).

Crescenta Valley d. Glendale, 25-14, 25-11, 25-13

Shereen Cline had six digs and 15 aces and Sandi Soderstrom had 13 assists, five digs and four aces for host Crescenta Valley (6-9, 3-3).

PACIFIC VIEW LEAGUE

Oxnard d. Camarillo, 21-25, 23-25, 27-25, 25-19, 15-13

Camille Soto had 14 kills, 22 assists and five aces and Mydori Saipale had 13 kills and three blocks to lead host Oxnard (5-5, 5-1), which avenged the earlier loss to Camarillo (4-2 in league) that broke a 60-match league winning streak.

PREP LEAGUE

Pasadena Poly d. Rio Hondo Prep, 25-11, 25-17, 25-19

Larkin Brogan had 11 kills and four aces to lead visiting Poly (11-5, 6-3) past Rio Hondo Prep (7-8 overall).

Westridge d. Mayfield, 25-22, 26-24, 25-22

Senior Gabrielle Bass had 13 kills and eight blocks, sophomore Kelly McCall had seven kills and six blocks and setter Annie Thorne had 27 assists and four aces to lead host Westridge (13-5, 4-4).

RIO HONDO LEAGUE

La Canada d. San Marino, 25-12, 25-12, 25-17

Annie Hillier had 15 kills and Morgan Anderson added eight kills and had four of the team’s 15 aces to lead La Canada (9-7, 6-0) past San Marino (4-2 in league play).

South Pasadena d. Blair, 25-10, 25-12, 25-3

Megan Baumgarten had seven kills and two aces, Megan Feldmeth had eight aces and Claudia Luck had four aces to lead South Pasadena (6-7, 3-3).

SAN ANTONIO LEAGUE

Walnut d. Rowland, 25-6, 25-12, 25-19

Janessa Currier had 10 kills for host Walnut (10-2, 5-0) as they defeated Rowland (5-6, 2-3).

SAN GABRIEL VALLEY LEAGUE

Gahr d. Paramount, 25-5, 25-21, 25-14

Senior outside hitter Monica Cordova had 24 kills and two aces and senior setter Louise DeLeon had 30 assists to lead host Gahr (18-11, 4-2) past Paramount (4-9, 2-4).

SAN JOAQUIN LEAGUE

Connelly d. Orangewood, 25-7, 25-10, 25-19

Freshman Lilla Frederich had eight kills, Liz Lizzari added seven kills and Sara Teal had 10 aces to lead host Connelly (12-5, 5-0).

SEA VIEW LEAGUE

Laguna Hills d. Irvine, 25-20, 25-27, 25-16, 11-25, 15-13

Outside hitter Michelle Lee had a match-high 20 kills while middle blocker Kinsey Johnson added nine kills and middle blocker Jasmine Douglass had eight for Laguna Hills (11-8, 2-4). Meghan Morere also served four aces for the Hawks.

Newport Harbor d. Foothill, 25-15, 15-25, 25-19, 22-25, 15-12

Stephanie Trinen had 10 kills to lead Newport Harbor (8-7, 5-1) to the victory.

SERRA LEAGUE

Lakewood St. Joseph d. Bishop Montgomery, 25-21, 27-25, 25-18

Ashley Ferrell had 10 kills and six digs and Barbie Thierjung finsihed with seven kills, two blocks and five digs for Bishop Montgomery (17-5, 1-5) in the loss to visiting St. Joseph (15-4, 4-2).

SIERRA LEAGUE

St. Lucy’s d. Ayala, 25-16, 25-13, 18-25, 24-26, 15-10Grace Urane had 35 assists and Liz Dworak added 22 digs as visiting St. Lucy’s, ranked No. 10 in Division III-AA, raised its record to 16-3, 6-0. Ayala fell to 4-8, 3-3.

SOUTH COAST LEAGUE

San Clemente d. Trabuso Hills, 25-12, 25-10, 25-21

Torey Ellick had 12 kills and two blocks, Carly Bergquist added 10 kills and Sara Hoffman finished with 35 assists and five digs to lead San Clemente (15-7, 6-0) over visiting Trabuco Hills (2-14, 0-6).

SUNSET LEAGUE

Edison d. Fountain Valley, 25-18, 25-16, 25-16

Senior Lindsey Carter had 10 kills to pace the host Chargers (16-3, 5-1), ranked No. 3 in the Southern Section Division II-AA coaches’ poll. Fountain Valley fell to 0-6 in league.

Huntington Beach d. Marina, 25-16, 25-20, 25-13

Shannon Hybl had 11 kills to lead Huntington Beach (7-7, 3-3) in the match at Marina (1-5 in league). The Oilers are the No. 4-ranked team in the Division II-A coaches’ poll.

Los Alamitos d. Esperanza, 25-23, 26-24, 25-14

In a rematch of last year’s Div. I-AA finals, Rachael Junior had 12 kills, Gena Urango had eight kills and 10 blocks and Bethany Keisner added six kills and 12 blocks for Los Alamitos (19-4, 6-0). As a team Los Alamitos, No. 1 in Division I-AA, had 45 blocks and 41 digs. Esperanza, No. 2 in Division I-AA, fell to 22-4, 3-3.

TRI-VALLEY LEAGUE

La Reina d. Oak Park, 25-15, 16-25, 25-19, 26-24

NONLEAGUE

St. Margaret’s d. Brentwood, 25-20, 19-25, 25-23, 26-24

Callan Smith had 13 kills and seven blocks for visiting St. Margaret’s (14-5), which is ranked No. 3 in Division IV-A, in a victory over No. 2 Brentwood (16-3). Jessica Fishburn had 15 kills to lead Brentwood.

Wednesday, Oct. 20

FREEWAY LEAGUE

Sonora d. La Habra, 25-22, 25-16, 26-28, 25-23

Junior outside hitter Kayleen Webster had 21 kills in the match for host Sonora (11-4, 4-2).

Troy d. Sunny Hills, 25-13, 22-25, 25-18, 25-12

Kelly Russell and Nicole DeCuir each had 13 kills to lead Troy (4-2 in league). Sunny Hills drops to 3-3 in league.

GOLDEN WEST LEAGUE

Santa Ana d. Costa Mesa, 26-24, 25-20, 25-15

Monica Braun had eight kills to lead host Santa Ana (10-2, 7-1). With the victory, The Saints are alone in second place in the league behind Ocean View. Costa Mesa drops to 6-4 overall and 5-3 in league.

HI-LO LEAGUE

Baker Valley d. Trona, 25-9, 25-16, 24-26, 25-9

Ashlie Miller had 12 kills and nine aces and Michelle Camacho had 16 assists to lead host Baker Valley (9-2, 8-1), which is tied with Immanuel Christian for first place in the league.

MARMONTE LEAGUE

Westlake d. Royal, 25-20, 23-25, 25-23, 25-20

Jillian Lane had 24 kills and Tawny Summers added 12 digs and 10 kills for host Westlake (7-4, 6-3).

MISSION LEAGUE

Flintridge Sacred Heart d. Sherman Oaks Notre Dame, 32-30, 25-20, 25-21

Kelly Smiland had 16 kills and Sam Orlandini had 39 assists to lead Flintridge Sacred Heart (10-2, 5-0) at Sherman Oaks Notre Dame (4-1). Flintridge Sacred Heart takes sole possesion of first place in league with the victory.

MONTVIEW LEAGUE

Gladstone d. Sierra Vista, 25-20, 25-13, 25-20

Mary Lind had 10 kills and five service aces to lead Gladstone (20-0, 8-0) at Sierra Vista (3-4 in league).

MOUNTAIN VIEW LEAGUE

Corona Santiago d. Corona, 25-14, 25-13, 25-13

Junior outside hitter Karliegh Delong had 13 kills and senior setter Devon Sutherland had 11 kills and 34 assists to lead Corona Santiago (13-2, 6-0) at Corona (2-8, 2-4). Santiago is alone atop the Mountain View League with four matches remaining.

OCEAN LEAGUE

Beverly Hills d. Culver City, 26-24, 25-21, 23-25, 21-25, 15-6Alison Munzer had 23 kills, five aces and five blocks to lead visiting Beverly Hills (8-6, 4-1). Culver City is 3-2 in league

PACIFIC COAST LEAGUE

Irvine University d. Santa Ana Calvary Chapel, 25-14, 25-6, 25-12

Sara Phares had eight kills and three blocks and setter Stephanie Brandt put up 19 assists and added five kills for visiting University (11-6, 2-4). Calvary Chapel is 2-12, 0-6 in league.

Northwood d. Laguna Beach, 25-19, 25-23, 26-24

Lindsay Macias had 19 kills and six aces and Alex Fell added 15 kills and four blocks for Northwood (16-6, 3-3). Laguna Beach is 11-7, 3-3 in league.

SOUTH COAST LEAGUE

Mission Viejo d. El Toro, 25-18, 25-9, 25-18

Adrienne Zielasko of Mission Viejo (11-5, 5-1) had nine kills and six blocks and teammate Kelly Bushman added nine kills at El Toro (2-4).

VALLE VISTA LEAGUE

Pomona d. Northview, 25-18, 25-15, 25-14

Jasmen Ward had 16 kills and five blocks and Markisha Richie added nine kills for visiting Pomona (11-3, 6-0). Christina Orozco had 35 assists for Pomona. Northview falls to 2-4 in league.

VALLEY LEAGUE

Pilibos d. Glendale Adventist, 25-20, 25-18, 25-22

Marie Tahanian had 11 kills and four service aces and Nayiri Keossian had 11 assists in the match for host Pilibos (10-8, 4-2). Glendale Adventist drops to 0-5 in league.

NONLEAGUE

Chadwick d. Whittier Christian, 25-18, 25-18, 25-22

Christina Swaney had six kills and Brooke McLeod served four aces in the loss for Whittier Christian (4-12). Chadwick improves to 10-1.

St. Monica d. Milken, 25-15, 18-25, 25-23, 25-20

Ellie Foran had 13 kills and 18 digs in the loss for Milken (11-3) at St. Monica.

West Valley Christian d. Southwestern Academy, 21-25, 17-25, 25-21, 25-23, 15-9

Ali Cole had 26 kills and six aces and Sydni Davis had 25 kills and four aces in the loss for host Southwestern Academy (7-2). West Valley Christian improves to 12-1.

Tuesday, Oct. 19

ACADEMY LEAGUE

Sage Hill d. Brethren Christian, 29-27, 25-21, 23-25, 25-17

Cat Dailey had 18 kills and four blocks for second-place Sage Hill (10-5, 4-1) which also got 14 kills, includind six in the decisive fourth game, from Haywood Wright. Rene Lee had nine kills for Brethren Christian (8-3, 3-2).

AGAPE LEAGUE

Bethel Christian d. Antelope Valley Christian, 25-8, 25-9, 25-8

Julie Stilson had 10 kills and six service aces and Taylor Messenger had 11 aces to lead host Bethel Christian (11-5, 4-1).

Hesperia Christian d. Victor Valley Christian, 25-23, 25-23, 26-24

Laura Gustin had 15 kills, four assits, three aces and 10 digs for Hisperia Christian (7-2, 6-0), ranked No. 2 in Div. V-AA. Sarah Lewis helped out in the victory with seven kills, 18 assists, two aces and five digs. Host Victor Valley Christian fell to 7-6, 2-3.

BASELINE LEAGUE

Alta Loma d. Los Osos, 25-19, 25-19, 25-16

Jennifer Fortuna had six kills and four digs for visiting Los Osos (8-7, 3-2). Alta Loma improved to 4-1 in league with the win.

BAY LEAGUE

Peninsula d. Leuzinger, 25-13, 25-16, 25-10

Mikki Jagd had 10 kills and Leslie Elgin served for 17 consecutive points in the third game to lead Peninsula (2-3 in league) at Leuzinger (0-4 in league).

BIG SKY LEAGUE

Linfield Christian d. Academy for Academic Excellence, 25-18, 25-18, 25-13

Stephanie Scheele had 12 kills to lead host Linfield Christian (8-3, 3-1) over Academy for Academic Excellence (0-4 in league).

CAMINO REAL LEAGUE

St. Matthias d. St. Bernard, 25-16, 25-16, 22-25, 26-24

Monique Arrington had 12 kills and five blocks for host St. Bernard (5-3, 3-1). St. Matthias improved to 7-1, 4-0, with the victory.

CENTURY LEAGUE

Brea d. El Modena, 25-22, 25-19, 18-25, 23-25, 15-13

Rachel Lumsden had 36 kills, 13 digs, three aces and three blocks, Amy Fink had 21 digs and four aces and Alison Aeschliman added 12 kills for visiting Brea (4-13, 3-2). Brittany Moore had 17 kills for El Modena (3-2 in league).

El Dorado d. Anaheim Canyon, 25-19, 25-14, 25-10

Shannan Homan had 13 kills and Jenna Friedrich had 26 assists for El Dorado (8-3, 5-0), ranked No. 2 in Div. II-AA. Canyon dropped to 1-4 in league.

CHRISTIAN LEAGUE

Ontario Christian d. Pomono Catholic, 25-14, 25-11, 25-6

Stacy Nanninga had seven kills and Alexa Antoni added 19 assists and seven aces for visiting Ontario Christian (4-7, 2-3).

DE ANZA LEAGUE

Yucca Valley d. Big Bear, 19-25, 27-25, 25-20, 25-23

Dani Rush, playing on injured knee, had eight kills and nine service aces and Nikita Johnson had five kills and three aces to lead host Yucca Valley (4-8, 3-7). Madison Bradley had 20 kills in the loss for Big Bear (5-8, 4-6). There was a 20 minute delay after the first point in the fourth game because of a power outage.

DELPHIC LEAGUE

Pacific Hills d. Montclair Prep, 19-25, 25-21, 25-23, 20-25, 15-8

Simone Shellmire had 21 kills and four blocks, Michelle Kries added nine aces, and freshman Abbey Lane had 17 digs for host Pacific Hills (6-6, 3-2) to put the Bruins in sole possession of third place in the league.

DEL REY LEAGUE

St. Paul d. St. Monica, 25-23, 25-23, 25-17

Host St. Paul was lead by Lisset Magdaleno who had 12 kills and seven blocks. St. Paul improved to 10-6, 3-1 with the win over St. Monica (7-4, 1-3).

DEL RIO LEAGUE

California d. Pioneer, 25-8, 25-21, 25-13

Brianna Gonzales had 13 kills to lead host California (12-2, 3-2) over Pioneer (1-8, 0-5).

Santa Fe d. La Serna, 25-13, 25-14, 25-23

Setter Marci Encinas had 29 assists in leading first-place Santa Fe (10-6, 5-0) to the home victory over La Serna (3-10, 1-4) at Sierra Adult School. The Chiefs are using the facility as their home gymnasium is undergoing a total renovation. Santa Fe continues to lead second-place El Rancho in the Del Rio League standings.

EMPIRE LEAGUE

Cypress d. Kennedy, 25-16, 25-22, 25-20

Kristin Kirkpatrick had nine kills to lead Cypress (9-12, 3-2).

Loara d. Katella, 25-21, 19-25, 25-18, 23-25, 15-8

Juli Miles had nine kills and Amanda Fama had eight kills to lead visiting Loara (8-7, 3-2) over Katella (1-4).

Orange Lutheran d. Valencia, 31-29, 17-25, 25-19, 15-25, 15-13

Roxi Ozolins had 14 kills and Lindsay Allen added 12 kills for visiting Orange Lutheran (4-1 in league). Jaque Davidsson had 17 kills for Valencia (4-1 in league).

FRONTIER LEAGUE

Nordhoff d. Santa Clara, 25-9, 25-13, 19-25, 25-13

Amie Cresto had six aces, 14 digs and 26 assists, Stephanie Flasch had 15 kills, 11 digs and five aces and Angelica Smith had 11 kills and six digs for visiting Nordhoff (8-3, 4-0).

Oaks Christian d. Malibu, 25-17, 25-12, 25-7

Julie Rubenstein put down 15 kills and had four aces and six digs in leading Oaks Christian (15-5, 3-1) to the home victory.

GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE

Bolsa Grande d. Los Amigos, 25-17, 19-25, 21-15, 25-18, 15-10

Cynthia Nguyen had 11 kills for host Bolsa Grande (8-6, 3-5) in the win over Los Amigos (5-10, 2-6).

Garden Grove Pacifica d. La Quinta, 25-22, 25-16, 25-20

Anne Lynn had 14 kills to lead the way for first-place Pacifica (10-2, 7-0). La Quinta dropped to 4-6, 4-4.

Rancho Alamitos d. Garden Grove Santiago, 25-15, 25-22, 25-11

Vaosa Lilii had 11 kills for Rancho Alamitos (12-2, 6-2), which is tied for second place in league with Garden Grove. Santiago dropped to 2-13, 0-8.

HARBOR LEAGUE

Lighthouse Christian d. Rolling Hills Prep, 25-20, 25-23, 25-21

Lighthouse Christian improves to 13-2, 7-0 in league.

HERITAGE LEAGUE

Milken d. Granada Hills Hillcrest Christian, 25-9, 25-21, 35-14

Brittany Adler of Milken (11-2, 4-0) had eight kills and 14 digs and teammate Nassim Hiekali added four aces and nine assists at Granada Hills Hillcrest Christian (1-3).
